# Frontend — Zoom Clone

## Stack

- Next.js App Router (`frontend/src/app/`)
- TypeScript strict, React 19 client components where needed (`"use client"`)
- Tailwind CSS v4 + semantic tokens in `globals.css` (`background`, `foreground`, `card`, `primary`, `meeting-*`)
- shadcn-style UI in `components/ui/`
- Lucide icons

## Architecture

- **Pages thin, logic in hooks** — `useMeeting` orchestrates API + WebSocket + WebRTC
- **REST** — `services/meeting-api.ts` only; no fetch scattered in components
- **Types** — shared in `types/meeting.ts` (including `SignalingMessage` union)
- **Rules** — client join/upcoming logic in `lib/meeting-rules.ts` (keep aligned with backend)

### Hook split

| Hook | Owns |
|------|------|
| `usePreJoinMedia` | Pre-join getUserMedia + toggles |
| `useWebRTC` | Local stream, peer connections, signaling handler, host state |
| `useWebSocket` | WS connect/send; enabled only after `isMediaReady` |
| `useMeeting` | Session, join/leave API, wires hooks together |

## UI conventions

- Dashboard: `DashboardNav` (logo, search, settings), `DashboardHero` (clock + actions), `MeetingList`
- Zoom blue primary: `#0E71EB` / `primary` token; orange for new meeting `#FF6B2C`
- Use semantic colors for dark mode — avoid hardcoded `bg-white` / `#F7F9FC` without `dark:` or tokens
- Required form fields: `required` prop on `FormField` + red `RequiredMark` asterisk; description stays optional
- Meeting room: dark `meeting-*` tokens; local video always `muted`; remote audio must stay mounted when camera off (`VideoTile`)

## WebRTC rules

- Wait for `getUserMedia` before WebSocket connect and before creating offers/answers
- Mesh topology: one `RTCPeerConnection` per remote peer
- Broadcast mic/camera UI via `media-state` WS message (remote track `enabled` is not reliable cross-browser)
- ICE: STUN only in `lib/config.ts` — document if adding TURN

## Component guidelines

- Prefer focused components under `components/dashboard/` and `components/meeting/`
- Colocate small helpers; avoid new one-line utility files
- Match existing naming: `PascalCase` components, `useCamelCase` hooks
- Do not add tests unless requested

## Env

```env
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
NEXT_PUBLIC_WS_URL=ws://localhost:8000
```

Production must use `https` / `wss`.

## Avoid

- Socket.io (native WebSocket only)
- Putting WebRTC signaling logic in JSX/components
- Unmounting `<video>` when remote camera is off (breaks audio)
- Duplicating meeting duration/join rules without checking `lib/meeting-rules.ts`
